SIMPLE: unexceptionable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unexceptionable
<hw>Unexceptionable</hw>  <def>See <er>exceptionable</er>.</def>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unexceptionable
<hw>Un`ex*cep"tion*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
liable to any exception or objection; unobjectionable; faultless; good;
excellent; <as>as, a man of most <ex>unexceptionable</ex>
character</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Un`ex*cep"tion*a*ble*ness</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> -- <wf>Un`ex*cep"tion*a*bly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1573 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Chesterfield is an <qex>unexceptionable</qex> witness.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unexceptive</ent>⟦br⟧
